Package io.jeo.filter

Filter and expression model.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Expression
    Derives a value from a given input.
    FilterVisitor<T>
    Visitor for filter classes.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    All<T>
    Identity filter that always returns true.
    BinaryFilter<T>
    Base class for filters that involve a left and a right expression.
    BooleanFilterAdapter
    Filter adapter that returns Boolean from each visit method and stubs out all calls returning false.
    Comparison<T>
    Filter that applies a binary comparison operator to two expression operands.
    Filter<T>
    Predicate that applies a boolean filter for a given input.
    FilterAdapter<T>
    Adapter for FilterVisitor that stubs all methods.
    FilterBuilder
    Builder for filters that can compose complex filter / expression trees.
    Filters
    Filter utility class.
    FilterSplitter
    Splits a filter into two parts based on criteria provided by a filter visitor.
    FilterWalker<T>
    Adapter for FilterVisitor that walks filters and expressions that are composed of other filters/expressions.
    Function
    Expression that evaluates to the result of a function.
    Id<T>
    Filter for matching Feature objects by id.
    In<T>
    'In' predicate filter.
    Like<T>
    'Like' predicate filter.
    Literal
    Static expression that evaluates to a literal value.
    Logic<T>
    Filter that applies a logical operator to a set of expressions.
    Math  
    Mixed
    An expression composed of other expressions.
    None<T>
    Identity filter that always returns false.
    Null<T>
    Implementation of IS NULL and IS NOT NULL.
    Property
    Evaluates a field/property of a Feature object.
    Self
    Expression that just returns the value passed into it.
    Spatial<T>
    Filter that applies a spatial comparison operator to two geometry expression operands.
    StrictFilterAdapter<T>
    Adapter for FilterVisitor that stubs each method with a UnsupportedOperationException.
    TypeOf<T>
    Filter that tests the type of an object.
